  "text": "Concerning ET, Gangat et al. [CITATION_1] identified anemia, extreme thrombocytosis (>1000 × 10 9 L), and age as independent risk factors for leukemic transformation in this subset of MPN patients. In detail, the risk of leukemic transformation was low at 0.4% if both the aforementioned risk factors were absent, and was significantly higher at 4.8% and 6.5% in the presence of one or both risk factors, respectively (p < 0.001). Interestingly, many important retrospective case series have supported the absence of any convincing evidence for drug leukemogenicity in ET [CITATION_2] , even though reports to the contrary have also to be mentioned [CITATION_3] .",
